>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Egyptian Mythology — Ancient Power Plays","description":"Egyptian mythology words valid in Scrabble with point values. SPHINX 18pts, ANKH 11pts, JACKAL 19pts, PHARAOH 15pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-egyptian"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is JACKAL a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! JACKAL scores 19 points (J=8, A=1, C=3, K=5, A=1, L=1). It refers to the wild dog associated with Anubis, the Egyptian god of the dead. The J and K tiles combine for 13 of the 19 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is SPHINX worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SPHINX scores 18 points (S=1, P=3, H=4, I=1, N=1, X=8). The mythical creature with a human head and lion body. The X tile (8pts) and H tile (4pts) provide the bulk of the score."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is ANKH valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. ANKH scores 11 points (A=1, N=1, K=5, H=4) and is the Egyptian cross symbol of life. At just 4 letters with K and H, it delivers excellent points-per-tile efficiency."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Egyptian Mythology — Ancient Power Plays</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Egyptian mythology offers some of the highest-scoring thematic words in Scrabble. JACKAL combines J and K for 19 points, SPHINX delivers 18 with its X tile, and ANKH packs 11 points into just 4 letters. These words are culturally iconic — everyone knows what a sphinx or an ankh is — making them easy to recall under game pressure.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JACKAL (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SPHINX</p></div>
