          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PHARAOH</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Egyptian Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JACKAL — 19 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">J=8, A=1, C=3, K=5, A=1, L=1 · 6 letters · J+K combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The wild dog sacred to Anubis, Egyptian god of the afterlife. JACKAL uses two of the game's premium consonants — J (8pts) and K (5pts) — in a single word. At 3.2 points per tile, it's an exceptional way to clear both tiles at once.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦁 SPHINX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · S=1, P=3, H=4, I=1, N=1, X=8 · Mythical guardian</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">☥ ANKH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · A=1, N=1, K=5, H=4 · Symbol of life</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👑 PHARAOH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · P=3, H=4, A=1, R=1, A=1, O=1, H=4 · Egyptian ruler</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🐍 COBRA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · C=3, O=1, B=3, R=1, A=1 · Sacred serpent</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Egyptian Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MUMMY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SCARAB</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OASIS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LOTUS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PAPYRUS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JACKAL clears J and K together:</span> Having both J and K on your rack is brutal. JACKAL solves both problems in one play for 19 points. The remaining tiles (A, C, A, L) are all common and easy to draw.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SPHINX uses X in a consonant cluster:</span> The PH-I-NX pattern means you don't need open vowel spots for the X. SPHINX fits where other X words can't — between consonant-heavy areas of the board.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ANKH is a compact K+H play:</span> At just 4 letters, ANKH scores 11 points (2.75 per tile). It works on tight boards where longer words won't fit, and both K and H are hard tiles to place elsewhere.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Egyptian mythology words target <span class="text-white font-medium">the hardest premium tiles</span> — J (JACKAL), K (ANKH, JACKAL), X (SPHINX), and H (ANKH, PHARAOH, SPHINX). Memorise these four words and you have a plan for every difficult consonant in the bag.</p>
      </div>
